de.mrapp.android.adapter.datastructure.item

Class ItemListIterator<DataType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mrapp.android.adapter.datastructure.item.ItemListIterator<DataType>
  • Type Parameters:
    DataType - The type of the items' data
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<DataType>, java.util.ListIterator<DataType>

    public class ItemListIterator<DataType>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.ListIterator<DataType>
    A list iterator, which allows to iterate the data of items, which are contained by a list. When the iterated list is modified, the underlying data of the adapter, the items belong to, is also modified.
    Since:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Michael Rapp

    • Constructor Detail

      • ItemListIterator

        public ItemListIterator(@NonNull
                        java.util.List<Item<DataType>> items,
                        @Nullable
                        ListAdapter<DataType> adapter,
                        int index)
        Creates a new list iterator, which allows to iterate the data of the item's which are contained by a list, starting at a specific index.
        Parameters:
        items - The list, which contains the items, whose data should be iterated, as an instance of the type List. The list may not be null
        adapter - The adapter, whose underlying data should be modified, when the list, which is iterated by the list iterator, is modified, as an instance of the type ListAdapter or null, if no adapter's underlying data should be modified
        index - The index, the iterator should start at, as an Integer value. The index must be at least 0 and at maximum the size of the given list - 1, otherwise an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown
